Program: Discovery
Title: Impossible Visions - the early universe
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p03jry88
Last Broadcast Date: 21 November 2002
The technology that makes the study of the unseen possible. Scientists can see the inner world of the atom, study your living brain as you think, and travel back in time to see the universe before the earth was born. This series examines the technology that makes all this possible. Presenter: Martin Redfern. Show less